ce:section.ce:para:
We assume given a historical data set (X, Y) of measurements of a building.
Y = { x ( k + 1 ) , … , x ( k + N ) }
consists of measurements of room temperatures x.
X = { u ( k ) , … , u ( k + N − 1 ) , d ( k − δ ) , … , d ( k + N − 1 ) , x ( k − δ ) , … , x ( k ) }
consists of measurements of data that potentially has an influence on Y. These are control inputs u (e.g. cooling energy), disturbances d (e.g. ambient temperature and solar radiation forecasts, but also time of day variables) and autoregressive terms of the room temperature x. N denotes the prediction horizon for the predictive controller, δ denotes the number of autoregressive terms.
